{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "easyvtc-ratings-sprint6",
    "name": "EasyVTC API — Évaluations (Sprint 6)",
    "description": "# EasyVTC — Module Évaluations (Ratings)\n\n## Endpoints couverts\n\n### Client\n- `POST /reservations/:id/rating`          → Soumettre une note 1–5 (course terminée)\n\n### Chauffeur\n- `GET  /drivers/me/ratings`               → Ses propres évaluations + moyenne\n\n### Admin / Manager\n- `GET  /admin/drivers/:id/ratings`         → Évaluations + moyenne d'un chauffeur\n- `GET  /admin/ratings`                    → Liste globale de toutes les évaluations\n- `DELETE /admin/ratings/:id`              → Supprimer une évaluation\n\n## Prérequis\n1. Lancer l'API : `npm run dev`\n2. Avoir dans Supabase : un compte client, driver (avec profil drivers), admin\n3. Avoir au moins une réservation en statut `completed` assignée au driver\n\n## Ordre d'exécution recommandé\n1. 🔐 Setup — Tokens\n2. 🔍 Setup — IDs (réservation terminée + driver_id)\n3. ⭐ Client — Soumettre une évaluation\n4. 🚗 Chauffeur — Voir ses évaluations\n5. 👨‍💼 Admin — Gestion des évaluations\n6. 🔒 Contrôle d'accès\n\n## Variables sauvegardées automatiquement\n- `client_token`, `driver_token`, `admin_token`\n- `reservation_id` (completed), `driver_id` (drivers.id)\n- `rating_id`",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "base_url",       "value": "http://localhost:4000", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "client_token",   "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "driver_token",   "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "admin_token",    "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "reservation_id", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "driver_id",      "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "rating_id",      "value": "", "type": "string" }
  ],
  "item": [

    {
      "name": "🔐 Setup — Tokens",
      "description": "Connexion des 3 rôles. Les tokens sont sauvegardés en variables de collection.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Login Client",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/login", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["auth", "login"] },
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"client@test.com\",\n  \"password\": \"Client1234!\"\n}" }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "pm.test('client_token sauvegardé', () => {",
            "  const { ok, data } = pm.response.json();",
            "  pm.expect(ok).to.be.true;",
            "  pm.collectionVariables.set('client_token', data.access_token);",
            "  console.log('client_token OK — user_id:', data.user?.id);",
            "});"
          ]}}]
        },
        {
          "name": "Login Driver",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/login", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["auth", "login"] },
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"driver@test.com\",\n  \"password\": \"Driver1234!\"\n}" }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "pm.test('driver_token sauvegardé', () => {",
            "  const { ok, data } = pm.response.json();",
            "  pm.expect(ok).to.be.true;",
            "  pm.collectionVariables.set('driver_token', data.access_token);",
            "  console.log('driver_token OK');",
            "});"
          ]}}]
        },
        {
          "name": "Login Admin",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/login", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["auth", "login"] },
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"admin@test.com\",\n  \"password\": \"Admin1234!\"\n}" }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "pm.test('admin_token sauvegardé', () => {",
            "  const { ok, data } = pm.response.json();",
            "  pm.expect(ok).to.be.true;",
            "  pm.collectionVariables.set('admin_token', data.access_token);",
            "  console.log('admin_token OK');",
            "});"
          ]}}]
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "name": "🔍 Setup — IDs (réservation terminée + driver_id)",
      "description": "Récupère une réservation completed du client et sauvegarde reservation_id + driver_id (drivers.id).\nSi aucune n'existe, les saisir manuellement dans les variables de collection.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET mes réservations completed (client)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{client_token}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/reservations/mine?status=completed&limit=5",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["reservations", "mine"],
              "query": [{ "key": "status", "value": "completed" }, { "key": "limit", "value": "5" }]
            }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "pm.test('reservation_id et driver_id sauvegardés', () => {",
            "  const { ok, data } = pm.response.json();",
            "  pm.expect(ok).to.be.true;",
            "  const list = data.reservations ?? data.data ?? (Array.isArray(data) ? data : []);",
            "  if (Array.isArray(list) && list.length > 0) {",
            "    const resa = list[0];",
            "    pm.collectionVariables.set('reservation_id', resa.id);",
            "    if (resa.driver_id) pm.collectionVariables.set('driver_id', resa.driver_id);",
            "    console.log('reservation_id:', resa.id, '| driver_id:', resa.driver_id);",
            "  } else {",
            "    console.warn('⚠️ Aucune réservation completed — saisir reservation_id et driver_id manuellement');",
            "  }",
            "});"
          ]}}]
        },
        {
          "name": "GET liste chauffeurs (admin) — récupérer driver_id",
          "description": "Alternative si le driver_id n'est pas dans la réservation. Sauvegarde le premier driver_id de la liste.",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{admin_token}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/admin/drivers?limit=5",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["admin", "drivers"],
              "query": [{ "key": "limit", "value": "5" }]
            }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "pm.test('driver_id sauvegardé', () => {",
            "  const { ok, data } = pm.response.json();",
            "  pm.expect(ok).to.be.true;",
            "  const list = data.drivers ?? data.data ?? (Array.isArray(data) ? data : []);",
            "  if (Array.isArray(list) && list.length > 0) {",
            "    pm.collectionVariables.set('driver_id', list[0].id);",
            "    console.log('driver_id (drivers.id):', list[0].id);",
            "  } else {",
            "    console.warn('⚠️ Aucun chauffeur trouvé — saisir driver_id manuellement');",
            "  }",
            "});"
          ]}}]
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "name": "⭐ Client — Soumettre une évaluation",
      "description": "POST /reservations/:id/rating\nLe client note le chauffeur après une course terminée (note 1–5 étoiles).",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "[Client] POST note 5/5 — OK ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{client_token}}" },
              { "key": "Content-Type",  "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/reservations/{{reservation_id}}/rating",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["reservations", "{{reservation_id}}", "rating"]
            },
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"note\": 5\n}" }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
            "pm.test('Évaluation créée', () => {",
            "  const { ok, data } = pm.response.json();",
            "  pm.expect(ok).to.be.true;",
            "  pm.expect(data).to.have.property('id');",
            "  pm.expect(data.note).to.equal(5);",
            "  pm.expect(data.reservation_id).to.equal(pm.collectionVariables.get('reservation_id'));",
            "  pm.expect(data.driver_id).to.be.a('string');",
            "  pm.expect(data.client_id).to.be.a('string');",
            "  pm.expect(data.created_at).to.be.a('string');",
            "  pm.collectionVariables.set('rating_id', data.id);",
            "  console.log('rating_id:', data.id, '| note:', data.note);",
            "});"
          ]}}]
        },
        {
          "name": "[Client] POST note 3/5 (autre réservation) — OK ⭐⭐⭐",
          "description": "Tester avec une autre réservation completed. Adapter reservation_id manuellement si besoin.",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{client_token}}" },
              { "key": "Content-Type",  "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/reservations/{{reservation_id}}/rating",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["reservations", "{{reservation_id}}", "rating"]
            },
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"note\": 3\n}" }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "const status = pm.response.code;",
            "pm.test('201 créée ou 409 doublon attendu', () => {",
            "  pm.expect(status).to.be.oneOf([201, 409]);",
            "  console.log('Résultat attendu — code:', status);",
            "});"
          ]}}]
        },
        {
          "name": "[409] Double notation — même réservation",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{client_token}}" },
              { "key": "Content-Type",  "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/reservations/{{reservation_id}}/rating",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["reservations", "{{reservation_id}}", "rating"]
            },
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"note\": 1\n}" }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 409 — déjà évaluée', () => pm.response.to.have.status(409));",
            "pm.test('ok = false', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().ok).to.be.false);",
            "pm.test('Message doublon', () => {",
            "  const { message } = pm.response.json();",
            "  pm.expect(message).to.include('évaluée');",
            "});"
          ]}}]
        },
        {
          "name": "[400] Note invalide — 0 (hors plage 1–5)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{client_token}}" },
              { "key": "Content-Type",  "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/reservations/{{reservation_id}}/rating",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["reservations", "{{reservation_id}}", "rating"]
            },
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"note\": 0\n}" }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 400 — note < 1', () => pm.response.to.have.status(400));",
            "pm.test('ok = false', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().ok).to.be.false);",
            "pm.test('Erreur sur le champ note', () => {",
            "  const body = pm.response.json();",
            "  pm.expect(body.errors?.note ?? body.message).to.exist;",
            "});"
          ]}}]
        },
        {
          "name": "[400] Note invalide — 6 (hors plage 1–5)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{client_token}}" },
              { "key": "Content-Type",  "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/reservations/{{reservation_id}}/rating",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["reservations", "{{reservation_id}}", "rating"]
            },
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"note\": 6\n}" }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 400 — note > 5', () => pm.response.to.have.status(400));",
            "pm.test('ok = false', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().ok).to.be.false);"
          ]}}]
        },
        {
          "name": "[400] Note manquante — body vide",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{client_token}}" },
              { "key": "Content-Type",  "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/reservations/{{reservation_id}}/rating",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["reservations", "{{reservation_id}}", "rating"]
            },
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{}" }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 400 — note manquante', () => pm.response.to.have.status(400));",
            "pm.test('ok = false', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().ok).to.be.false);"
          ]}}]
        },
        {
          "name": "[400] Note décimale (non entier)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{client_token}}" },
              { "key": "Content-Type",  "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/reservations/{{reservation_id}}/rating",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["reservations", "{{reservation_id}}", "rating"]
            },
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"note\": 4.5\n}" }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 400 — note non entière', () => pm.response.to.have.status(400));",
            "pm.test('ok = false', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().ok).to.be.false);"
          ]}}]
        },
        {
          "name": "[400] reservation_id invalide (pas UUID)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{client_token}}" },
              { "key": "Content-Type",  "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/reservations/not-a-uuid/rating",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["reservations", "not-a-uuid", "rating"]
            },
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"note\": 4\n}" }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 400 — UUID invalide', () => pm.response.to.have.status(400));",
            "pm.test('ok = false', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().ok).to.be.false);"
          ]}}]
        },
        {
          "name": "[404] Réservation inexistante (UUID valide inconnu)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{client_token}}" },
              { "key": "Content-Type",  "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/reservations/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/rating",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["reservations", "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000", "rating"]
            },
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"note\": 4\n}" }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 404 — réservation inconnue', () => pm.response.to.have.status(404));",
            "pm.test('ok = false', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().ok).to.be.false);"
          ]}}]
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "name": "🚗 Chauffeur — Voir ses évaluations",
      "description": "GET /drivers/me/ratings\nLe chauffeur consulte ses propres notes et sa moyenne.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "[Driver] GET /drivers/me/ratings — page 1",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{driver_token}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/drivers/me/ratings?page=1&limit=20",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["drivers", "me", "ratings"],
              "query": [{ "key": "page", "value": "1" }, { "key": "limit", "value": "20" }]
            }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "pm.test('Structure paginée correcte', () => {",
            "  const { ok, data } = pm.response.json();",
            "  pm.expect(ok).to.be.true;",
            "  pm.expect(data.ratings).to.be.an('array');",
            "  pm.expect(data.total).to.be.a('number');",
            "  pm.expect(data.page).to.equal(1);",
            "  pm.expect(data.limit).to.equal(20);",
            "  pm.expect(data.total_pages).to.be.a('number');",
            "  console.log('Total évaluations:', data.total, '| Moyenne:', data.avg_note);",
            "});",
            "pm.test('avg_note est un nombre ou null', () => {",
            "  const { data } = pm.response.json();",
            "  if (data.avg_note !== null) {",
            "    pm.expect(data.avg_note).to.be.a('number');",
            "    pm.expect(data.avg_note).to.be.at.least(1);",
            "    pm.expect(data.avg_note).to.be.at.most(5);",
            "  }",
            "});",
            "pm.test('Chaque évaluation a les champs attendus', () => {",
            "  const { data } = pm.response.json();",
            "  if (data.ratings.length > 0) {",
            "    const r = data.ratings[0];",
            "    ['id','reservation_id','client_id','driver_id','note','created_at',",
            "     'client_first_name','client_last_name','reservation_scheduled_at'].forEach(k => {",
            "      pm.expect(r, `champ manquant: ${k}`).to.have.property(k);",
            "    });",
            "    pm.expect(r.note).to.be.within(1, 5);",
            "  }",
            "});",
            "pm.test('Évaluations triées DESC par created_at', () => {",
            "  const { data } = pm.response.json();",
            "  if (data.ratings.length >= 2) {",
            "    const t1 = new Date(data.ratings[0].created_at).getTime();",
            "    const t2 = new Date(data.ratings[1].created_at).getTime();",
            "    pm.expect(t1).to.be.at.least(t2);",
            "  }",
            "});"
          ]}}]
        },
        {
          "name": "[Driver] GET /drivers/me/ratings — pagination limit=1",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{driver_token}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/drivers/me/ratings?page=1&limit=1",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["drivers", "me", "ratings"],
              "query": [{ "key": "page", "value": "1" }, { "key": "limit", "value": "1" }]
            }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "pm.test('Limite appliquée', () => {",
            "  const { data } = pm.response.json();",
            "  pm.expect(data.ratings.length).to.be.at.most(1);",
            "  pm.expect(data.limit).to.equal(1);",
            "});"
          ]}}]
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "name": "👨‍💼 Admin — Gestion des évaluations",
      "description": "Endpoints admin/manager : vue par chauffeur, liste globale, suppression.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "[Admin] GET /admin/drivers/:id/ratings — évaluations d'un chauffeur",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{admin_token}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/admin/drivers/{{driver_id}}/ratings?page=1&limit=20",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["admin", "drivers", "{{driver_id}}", "ratings"],
              "query": [{ "key": "page", "value": "1" }, { "key": "limit", "value": "20" }]
            }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "pm.test('Structure paginée correcte', () => {",
            "  const { ok, data } = pm.response.json();",
            "  pm.expect(ok).to.be.true;",
            "  pm.expect(data.ratings).to.be.an('array');",
            "  pm.expect(data.total).to.be.a('number');",
            "  pm.expect(data.page).to.equal(1);",
            "  pm.expect(data.limit).to.equal(20);",
            "  pm.expect(data.total_pages).to.be.a('number');",
            "  console.log('Driver', pm.collectionVariables.get('driver_id'), '— évals:', data.total, '| avg_note:', data.avg_note);",
            "});",
            "pm.test('avg_note correct', () => {",
            "  const { data } = pm.response.json();",
            "  if (data.avg_note !== null) {",
            "    pm.expect(data.avg_note).to.be.a('number');",
            "    pm.expect(data.avg_note).to.be.within(1, 5);",
            "  }",
            "});",
            "pm.test('Chaque évaluation a les champs attendus', () => {",
            "  const { data } = pm.response.json();",
            "  if (data.ratings.length > 0) {",
            "    const r = data.ratings[0];",
            "    ['id','reservation_id','client_id','driver_id','note','created_at',",
            "     'client_first_name','client_last_name','reservation_scheduled_at'].forEach(k => {",
            "      pm.expect(r, `champ manquant: ${k}`).to.have.property(k);",
            "    });",
            "    pm.expect(r.note).to.be.within(1, 5);",
            "    if (!pm.collectionVariables.get('rating_id') && r.id) {",
            "      pm.collectionVariables.set('rating_id', r.id);",
            "      console.log('rating_id récupéré via admin:', r.id);",
            "    }",
            "  }",
            "});"
          ]}}]
        },
        {
          "name": "[Admin] GET /admin/drivers/:id/ratings — page 2",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
